# OA-001 — Foundational Objective

## Status

Foundational.

## Objective

Increase the structural cost required for an operator to sustain a false or materially incomplete narrative about the origin of a decision without proportional risk of detection by parties independent from that operator.

---

## Jurisdictional Boundary

This protocol operates on the traceability and reconstructability of decision narratives.

The selection of which decisions are subject to the protocol is external to the protocol itself and belongs to policy, contractual, regulatory, or organizational scope definitions.

---

## Non-Goals

This protocol does not guarantee:

- correctness of decisions;
- fairness of outcomes;
- institutional consequences following detection;
- adoption of any specific materiality framework.

---

## Rationale

The protocol addresses structural detectability, not institutional enforcement.
